rounded by beautiful countryside and situated just behind the city walls of the 'old town' in Santa Pau. Beautifully decorated in a traditional style, furnished with antique furniture and has a warm, welcoming atmosphere. The surroundings are great for outdoor enthusiasts. Located in the Garrotxa region with its many footpaths and trails along which you can discover the volcanic landscape and scenery of the nearby Nature Reserve.The rooms have an en suite bathroom, telephone, TV and heating. The rooms also overlook the garden and terrace, and the Garrotxa in the distance.Santa Pau (La Garrotxa) has a real village appearance, with relaxing streets and friendly local people. The village's location in an idyllic landscape makes it a real pleasure to visit and a great destination for exploring the regions beautiful countryside. Natural Park of La Garrotxa (15 km) - Easily reached in 10-20 minutes by car - the dormant volcanoes, fountains and the walking trail through the Fageda d'en Jorda beech forest make a great day trip.The Hotel also provides banquet facilities, bar, laundry service, lobby, non-smoking rooms, Free parking, reception, restaurant and room service.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>SurroundingArea</Type><Text>This hotel enjoys a peaceful and sunny location and guests will appreciate the lush vegetation. It is situated behind the historical walls in the centre of Santa Pau, in the ancient "Masia". El Prat de Llobregat airport is located about 172 km from the hotel and Gerona airport approximately 77 km.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>RoomTypes</Type><Text>Double Room - The Room offers 1 King or 2 Twin beds with color TV, ensuite/private bathroom, hairdryer, heating, laundry service, non-smoking rooms, room service and telephone.</Text></Description><Amenity><Code>Bar</Code><Text>Bar</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>ReceptionArea</Code><Text>Reception Area</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>ConferenceR